        <name>10.2.2.4 Polar form</name>
        <questiontext>&lt;p class="HELM_exercise"&gt;Exercise&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Consider the complex number \[z={@z1@} \] Evaluate the modulus of \(z\) \((r = |z|)\) and the principal value of the argument of \(z\ (\theta = \mathrm{Arg}(z)\)). Enter your results in the correct order, i.e. \([r,\theta]\).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;\([r,\theta] = \) [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]]&amp;nbsp;[[feedback:Result]]&lt;/p&gt;</questiontext>
        <questiontextformat>1</questiontextformat>
        <generalfeedback>&lt;p&gt;\[r=\sqrt{x^2+y^2}\] \[r=\sqrt{\left({@x@}\right)^2+\left({@y@}\right)^2}=\sqrt{{@x*x@}+{@y*y@}}\] \[r=\sqrt{@x*x+y*y@}={@rval@}\] \[\tan(\mathrm{arg}(z))=\frac{y}{x}=\frac{@y@}{@x@}={@y/x@}\] \[\mathrm{arg}(z)={@argsol@} + k\cdot\pi\] Considering the appropriate quadrant of the complex plane to fix \(k\), we find that \[\mathrm{arg}(z)={@principaltheta@}\].&lt;/p&gt;</generalfeedback>
